# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

> [!NOTE]
> Mermaid diagrams below follow the **alpha-prefix node rule** (no reserved keywords as node IDs, no markdown inside double-quoted labels). All node IDs are alphanumeric and prefixed with `s`/`l`/`c`/`p` to guarantee valid rendering.

## 4.1 Master Control Flow — Overall Program Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A([Program Start]) --> B[Read argv 1 as head]
    B --> C{Valid head 0 to 4999?}
    C -->|No| D[Print usage error and exit]
    C -->|Yes| E[Seed srand with time null]
    E --> F[Generate 10 random requests 0 to 4999]
    F --> G[Print request queue]
    G --> H1[Run SSTF and print trace]
    G --> H2[Run LOOK and print trace]
    G --> H3[Run CSCAN and print trace]
    H1 --> I[Print total head movement for each]
    H2 --> I
    H3 --> I
    I --> J([Program End])
```

## 4.2 SSTF Algorithm Flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    sStart([SSTF Start]) --> sInit[Set current = head<br/>Set done array to 0<br/>Set total = 0]
    sInit --> sLoop{i less than n?}
    sLoop -->|No| sRet[Return total]
    sLoop -->|Yes| sSearch[Search unserviced request<br/>with minimum abs distance]
    sSearch --> sPick[Pick request rBest]
    sPick --> sAdd[total = total + distance<br/>current = rBest<br/>Mark rBest as done]
    sAdd --> sPrint[Print step trace]
    sPrint --> sInc[i = i + 1]
    sInc --> sLoop
    sRet --> sEnd([SSTF End])
```

## 4.3 LOOK Algorithm Flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    lStart([LOOK Start]) --> lSort[Sort requests ascending]
    lSort --> lSplit[Find split point p<br/>first request greater or equal head]
    lSplit --> lAsc{i less than n?}
    lAsc -->|No| lDesc{i greater or equal 0?}
    lAsc -->|Yes| lAscBody[Move head to sorted i<br/>Add distance to total]
    lAscBody --> lAscInc[i = i + 1]
    lAscInc --> lAsc
    lDesc -->|No| lRet[Return total]
    lDesc -->|Yes| lDescBody[Move head to sorted i<br/>Add distance to total]
    lDescBody --> lDescDec[i = i - 1]
    lDescDec --> lDesc
    lRet --> lEnd([LOOK End])
```

## 4.4 C-SCAN Algorithm Flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    cStart([CSCAN Start]) --> cSort[Sort requests ascending]
    cSort --> cSplit[Find split point p<br/>first request greater or equal head]
    cSplit --> cAsc{i less than n?}
    cAsc -->|No| cToEnd
    cAsc -->|Yes| cAscBody[Service sorted i<br/>Add distance to total]
    cAscBody --> cAscInc[i = i + 1]
    cAscInc --> cAsc
    cToEnd[Move head to cylinder 4999<br/>Add distance to total] --> cJump[Jump head to cylinder 0<br/>Add 4999 to total]
    cJump --> cSecond{j less than p?}
    cSecond -->|No| cRet[Return total]
    cSecond -->|Yes| cSecBody[Service sorted j<br/>Add distance to total]
    cSecBody --> cSecInc[j = j + 1]
    cSecInc --> cSecond
    cRet --> cEnd([CSCAN End])
```

## 4.5 Block-Level Functional Architecture — Disk Scheduler Subsystem

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph INPUT[Input Layer]
        pA[Command Line Parser]
        pB[Random Request Generator]
    end
    subgraph CORE[Scheduling Core]
        pC[Request Queue Manager]
        pD[SSTF Engine]
        pE[LOOK Engine]
        pF[CSCAN Engine]
    end
