### ✅ Model Solution — Choice B

#### Part (a) — SSTF Trace for Small Disk

| Step | Current Head | Closest Request | Distance |
|---:|---:|---:|---:|
| 1 | 53 | 65 | 12 |
| 2 | 65 | 67 | 2 |
| 3 | 67 | 37 | 30 |
| 4 | 37 | 14 | 23 |
| 5 | 14 | 98 | 84 |
| 6 | 98 | 122 | 24 |
| 7 | 122 | 124 | 2 |
| 8 | 124 | 183 | 59 |

**Total:**

$$
D_{\text{SSTF}} = 12 + 2 + 30 + 23 + 84 + 24 + 2 + 59 = 236 \text{ cylinders}
$$

---

#### Part (b) — Worst-Case Response Time Comparison

| Algorithm | Worst-Case Response Time | Fairness |
|---|---|---|
| **FCFS** | $O(n \cdot \text{max\_distance})$ — every request waits for all prior ones | ✅ Highest (no preference) |
| **SSTF** | **Unbounded** — new requests near head can starve distant ones | ❌ Lowest |
| **SCAN** | $O(2 \cdot \text{max\_disk\_cylinders})$ — bounded by a full sweep | ✅ Good |
| **C-SCAN** | $O(2 \cdot \text{max\_disk\_cylinders})$ — bounded by a full sweep + wrap | ✅✅ Best (uniform) |

**Best fairness:** **C-SCAN**, because every request waits for at most one full outward sweep plus one wrap-around, regardless of its cylinder position. For example, a request at cylinder 10 and a request at cylinder 4990 will both be serviced within the same time bound, which is not guaranteed in SSTF.

